@node "NEW YORK WARRIORS"
NEW YORK WARRIORS

Stay all the way to the right on level 4 to reach the subway without much
trouble.
@endnode
@node "NEW ZEALAND STORY"
NEW ZEALAND STORY

On the title screen, press `Del' then `M'. Then type "FLUFFY KIWIS".

A 2nd cheat is to pause the game, and press `M'.  You should hear a laser gun
sound.  Type "MOTHERFUCKENKIWIBASTARDS".  Unlimited lives are yours.

Note: Another cheat starts the word as "MUTH...".  Another file (this could
be for the ST version says type "FLYFFY KIWIS" (including space) at any time
for infinite lives.

Hold 'SHIFT' and type "PHILLIP" on the title screen for mega firepower.

3rd cheat (hadn't heard this one before):

1. To access the cheat mode just press "TRY CHEATING" (including the space)
   keys together while on the title screen.  The border should turn grey and
   when you start the game you have infinite kiwi's and the ability to skip
   levels by pressing "<-".
2. Type either "DRATSABIWIKNEKCUFREHTOM" (this is backwards for tasteful and
   legal reasons) or "FLUFFY KIWIS".  Then press 'DEL', then 'M', then the
    code-word, and infinite kiwis shall be yours.

Has anyone heard of the whirl-winds?  They advance you levels.  Near the end
of level 1_1 there are three large steps that you must climb to reach your
brother (sister?), who is in a cage.  Stand at the left edge of the top step,
facing left and jump.  But as you jump, fire.  If your current weapon is
arrows, fire halfway up, but if your weapon is bombs, fire at the top of your
jump.  A whirl-wind should appear after four hits, and it will take you to
level 1_4.  Another source says:  On level 1, part 1, move to the area
containing three men with boomerangs and shoot them.  Go to the top of the
third platform, move to the left, jump and fire five times.  A whirlwind in a
box will appear, if you enter it, you will be transported to the end of the
level.  Then you can free Tiki's naughty friend just by jumping.  When you
reach the ice whale, move to the right-hand side of the spikes, avoid the
crystals, and wait until he picks you up.  Once inside the whale, you can
start shooting, but avoid the ice drops.  Meeting the rock monster without
bombs, makes him difficult to pass.  So collect bombs, go to the highest
platform and shoot it.  Kill it by either dodging the bullets and hitting it
when the doors open, or with fireballs.  The last boss you encounter is the
balloon seal.  He can't be killed, by blows to the body, so you must hit the
balloon.  Be careful, for the balloon seal is armed with a cannon and shoots
cannon balls at Tiki.

In 1_4, you will be in a little box under some water.  Go up and to the right
and you come out in a small room with three boxes on the right hand side.  Go
up these, and you will see 4 long spaces, the top one having an "N" and a "D"
in it.  Go up t o the top one, get the letters, stand in the centre of the
space, facing left, and fire.  Yep, you guessed it, another whirl-wind.  This
one takes you to level 2_4.  There are others, but I wont tell you - it would
spoil it!  But I will tell you that there is one on level 2_4.  Happy
hunting!

Or on level 2.4 , stand at the entrance to the room where the giant octopus
is located and fire to the right several times.  A warp will appear that will
take you to the beginning of level 3.1.

The town names are:

       AUCKLAND, ROTORUA, WAITOMO CAVES, STRAIT COOK, and MT COOK.

Try shooting arrows into certain clear areas because they can force a door
to appear. Jump into the door to enter a latter stage.

